31/07/2005
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Prime Minister Vlado Buckovski praised the constructive atmosphere of talks he held with leaders of opposition parties in parliament Friday (29 July). 
According to a statement from his office, Buckovski was satisfied with the results of the meetings that focused on key political and security issues. 
He particularly noted the climate of understanding and consensus regarding Macedonia's bid for membership in NATO and the EU. 
He also presented the government's positions on future constitutional amendments, including judicial reforms and presidential elections. 
The cabinet wants to ensure parliament adopts the changes by the end of October. 
(Vecer - 30/07/05; Macedonian Government Web site - 29/07/05)
